Evidence Synthesis Ireland:
Introduction to Risk of Bias 2.0

6th/7th July 2021 | Online | Facilitator: Luke McGuinness


Welcome to the course!

I am very much looking forward to meeting you all in early July!

Note that while there are no formal prerequisites for this course, I would encourage you to familiarise yourself with the example RCT we will be using throughout (see the Course Resources section). There will be (limited) time to read the paper on the day, but doing so in advance will allow you to jump straight into applying the RoB2 tool.

Course Resources

Example RCT: The DEMO trial

Over the course of the two days, we will assess an example published RCT using the RoB 2 tool. Details of this trial, plus PDF versions of the trial protocol and resulting publication, are provided below.

Citation: Krogh, Jesper, Bengt Saltin, and Merete Nordentoft. The DEMO trial: a randomized, parallel-group, observer-blinded clinical trial of strength versus aerobic versus relaxation training for patients with mild to moderate depression. The Journal of Clinical Psychiatry 70.6 (2009): 790-800.
